# WHAT IT IS
#   enventory is a CLI for managing project-scoped environment
#   variables centrally — instead of `.env` files scattered
#   around per-project repos, enventory persists them in a
#   single SQLite database, indexed by named "environments"
#   (e.g. `staging`, `production`, `my-laptop-dev`).  Each
#   environment has its own typed variables and "variable
#   references" (vars that point at another environment's
#   var, for safe cross-env reuse).  Then:
#     • `enventory shell zsh init` emits the zsh hook that
#       auto-exports the matching environment when you `cd`
#       into a project directory
#     • `enventory shell zsh chdir <DIR>` is the underlying
#       hook the auto-cd integration calls
#     • `enventory shell zsh export` / `unexport` flip the
#       current shell's exports manually
#     • `enventory exec` runs an arbitrary command with the
#       environment's vars injected (no shell hook needed)
#     • `enventory var create / delete / update / show /
#       ref ...` and `enventory env create / delete / list
#       / update / show` perform CRUD on the underlying
#       SQLite-backed store
#
#   The tooling is OpenTelemetry-instrumented end-to-end via
#   `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.44.0`, so every shell hook
#   invocation, SQLite query, and var-lookup span flows out
#   as OTLP/gRPC or OTLP/HTTP telemetry to a configured
#   collector — useful for tracking where shell-startup
#   latency comes from in a fleet of dev workstations.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from main.go `warg.New(...)`
#                       declaration + cli/*.go subcommand
#                       builders; extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       bbkane/enventory/contents/...`)
#
#   enventory <SECTION> [<SUBSECTION>...] <CMD> [args...]
#
#   Top-level structure:
#     completion zsh                 Print zsh completion script
#                                    (warg's built-in
#                                    completion-script emitter)
#
#     env <CMD>                      Environment commands
#       create <NAME>                  Create a new environment
#       delete <NAME>                  Delete an environment
#       list                           List all environments
#       update <NAME>                  Update an environment's
#                                      metadata
#       show <NAME>                    Show an environment's
#                                      vars + metadata
#
#     shell zsh <CMD>                Zsh-specific shell hooks
#       chdir <DIR>                    Underlying hook the
#                                      auto-cd integration
#                                      calls when the user
#                                      changes directory
#       init                           Emit the zsh
#                                      integration hook (eval
#                                      this in `.zshrc`)
#       export <ENV>                   Export the given
#                                      environment's vars into
#                                      the current shell
#       unexport <ENV>                 Unexport the given
#                                      environment's vars from
#                                      the current shell
#
#     var <CMD>                      Vars owned by a given
#                                    environment
#       create <NAME>=<VALUE>          Create a typed env var
#       delete <NAME>                  Delete a var
#       show <NAME>                    Show a var's value +
#                                      metadata
#       update <NAME>                  Update a var
#
#       ref <CMD>                    Variable references
#                                    (a var that points at
#                                    another environment's
#                                    var, for safe cross-env
#                                    reuse)
#         create <NAME>                Create a var reference
#         delete <NAME>                Delete a var reference
#         show <NAME>                  Show a var reference
#         update <NAME>                Update a var reference
#
#     exec <CMD> [ARGS...]           Run a command with the
#                                    environment's vars
#                                    injected (no shell hook
#                                    needed; ideal for
#                                    ad-hoc / CI invocations)
#
#   Help / version:
#     --help [--help detailed]       Show help (warg-style:
#                                    `--help detailed` for the
#                                    detailed variant)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.44.0` +
#   `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.44.0` declared in go.mod,
#   with the OTLP exporters
#   (`go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.37.0`
#   + `.../otlptracegrpc v1.37.0` + `.../otlptracehttp v1.37.0`)
#   and the stdout exporter (`.../stdout/stdouttrace v1.37.0`)
#   pulled in as transitive direct-usage deps — `opentelemetry-
#   go` is THE canonical Go implementation of the CNCF
#   OpenTelemetry specification, maintained by the OpenTelemetry
#   community at the open-telemetry/opentelemetry-go repository
#   (5,400+ stars; the predominant typed Go SDK for traces /
#   metrics / logs that every Go observability pipeline ends
#   up depending on — used by Bearer, daptin, pydio/cells,
#   koderover/zadig, go-dev-frame/sponge, thirdweb-dev/insight,
